  "local_port": 37460,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you find out what your zip code plus four is?",
  "response": "Finding your ZIP+4 code, the more precise version of your standard five-digit ZIP code, is fairly easy. Here are a few ways to find it:\n\n1. **Online Lookup Tools:** \n   - The United States Postal Service (USPS) offers an online ZIP Code lookup tool. You can access it on the USPS website. Enter your full address, and it will provide you with the ZIP+4 code.\n\n2. **Contact Local Post Office:**\n   - You can visit or contact your local post office and ask a representative to look up your ZIP+4 code. They have the necessary tools to provide this information.\n\n3. **Mail Delivered to Your Address:**\n   - If you have received mail that has your full ZIP code written on it, you can check it there. Often times, business correspondence and official documents will include the ZIP+4 code.\n\n4. **Utility Bills or Statements:**\n   - Sometimes utility bills, bank statements, and other official documents list the ZIP+4 code.\n\n5. **Property Databases or Real Estate Websites:**\n   - Real estate websites and property databases occasionally provide detailed ZIP+4 information for listed properties.\n\nWhen using online tools or asking for this information, ensure you provide your complete address to get the most accurate ZIP+4 code.",
